### curl equivalent (save output to meme.png)
# Use curl's -F which constructs multipart form data and sets the boundary automatically:
# curl -X POST "http://127.0.0.1:8000/meme-generation" -F "image=@D:/meme-generator/backend/tests/sample.jpg" -F "text=Hello from curl" -F "font_size=48" -F "color=white" -F "position=bottom" --output meme.png
